1
00:01:39,557 --> 00:01:40,767
<i>What's this?</i>

2
00:01:44,813 --> 00:01:47,398
<i>I'm not sensing
the same determination he had before.</i>

3
00:01:47,982 --> 00:01:49,567
<i>His fists are wavering.</i>

4
00:01:55,615 --> 00:01:58,451
You aren't taking this seriously, are you?

5
00:02:00,912 --> 00:02:03,456
-That's not wh...
-You aren't even trying to hit me.

6
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,834
And you're not even trying
to dodge my kicks.

7
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:08,586
<i>This fight...</i>

8
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:11,297
<i>I thought he knew everything
when he challenged us.</i>

9
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:13,758
<i>But that wasn't the case.</i>

10
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:16,845
<i>Then why did he beat them up?</i>

11
00:02:18,179 --> 00:02:19,514
<i>I want to know.</i>

12
00:02:20,682 --> 00:02:22,475
<i>I want to know more about him.</i>

13
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:27,522
Just what the hell are you trying to do?

14
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:34,237
Yeah, really...

15
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:38,116
just what am I trying to do?

16
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,244
Why did you beat them up?

17
00:02:41,578 --> 00:02:44,998
I thought your team was all about
strength equals freedom.

18
00:02:46,791 --> 00:02:48,418
That's right.

19
00:02:48,918 --> 00:02:51,296
This is the den of the strong.

20
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:59,679
It's not a place for scum.

21
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:14,152
<i>If the head loses his mind,
his limbs will stop moving properly.</i>

22
00:03:15,069 --> 00:03:19,532
<i>After I've spent my time
skinning away the scums out of our team.</i>

23
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:22,911
<i>And then...</i>

24
00:03:23,494 --> 00:03:27,040
<i>we picked a fight with Bofurin,
the team Choji has been obsessed with.</i>

25
00:03:35,298 --> 00:03:39,969
<i>I thought this fight
would trigger some changes.</i>

26
00:03:41,679 --> 00:03:46,309
<i>But I got everyone involved in this fight
where we have no justice.</i>

27
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:51,856
<i>Even so...</i>

28
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:53,942
<i>there's no turning back now.</i>

29
00:03:55,193 --> 00:03:56,236
<i>Since that day...</i>

30
00:03:57,111 --> 00:03:59,697
<i>I decided to hold on to this mistake...</i>

31
00:04:00,907 --> 00:04:03,660
<i>I can't possibly stop now.</i>

32
00:04:22,512 --> 00:04:25,098
<i>The emblem here's faded quite a bit...</i>

33
00:04:27,392 --> 00:04:30,395
Just what the hell are you trying to do?

34
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:33,982
Right...

35
00:04:54,794 --> 00:04:56,671
I wanna go to the mountains.

36
00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:58,548
Huh?

37
00:04:58,631 --> 00:05:00,925
What crap is that?

38
00:05:01,509 --> 00:05:04,304
You say this is not a place for scum...

39
00:05:04,387 --> 00:05:06,639
Then why are you here?

40
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:09,559
You better stop speaking nonsense.

41
00:05:09,642 --> 00:05:12,395
What you did is just as scummy as them.

42
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:15,356
Yeah, you're strong.

43
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:18,985
But you're lame as heck.

44
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:24,324
And I'll prove that to you by beating you!

45
00:05:24,991 --> 00:05:27,702
And then you'll stop
doing lame crap like this...

46
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:30,580
and become someone I want to fight.

47
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:32,623
A cool person!

48
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:39,047
You're really selfish, aren't you?

49
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:43,468
You've sure got a big mouth to say that to
someone who's leagues stronger than you.

50
00:05:43,551 --> 00:05:45,428
Who cares if it's selfish?

51
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:51,225
That's what it means
to push yourself in a fight!

52
00:05:53,019 --> 00:05:56,272
No matter how strong my opponent is...

53
00:05:56,814 --> 00:05:58,691
even if it's someone I owe my life to...

54
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:00,568
I won't look away...

55
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:04,489
or bend my will!

56
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:09,494
What makes you think so?

57
00:06:09,577 --> 00:06:11,287
Doing that won't make anyone stro...

58
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:12,830
I'm the leader, right?

59
00:06:13,456 --> 00:06:15,458
I'm the strongest one around.

60
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,376
I'm free.

61
00:06:18,294 --> 00:06:20,379
I won't submit to anyone.

62
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:22,423
I decide things around here.

63
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:25,802
If you won't listen, then leave.

64
00:06:40,149 --> 00:06:43,069
CAGE

65
00:07:04,465 --> 00:07:05,967
Fine.

66
00:07:07,718 --> 00:07:08,928
But...

67
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:12,557
I'll be the one to tell everyone
about your plans, Choji.

68
00:07:13,683 --> 00:07:15,977
I'll be the one to rip off their skin.

69
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:20,231
So, Choji...

70
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:23,151
please keep smiling with everyone.

71
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:41,586
You're really good...

72
00:07:42,336 --> 00:07:44,630
at getting on my nerves!

73
00:07:51,137 --> 00:07:52,513
I knew it.

74
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:56,184
You weren't being serious before.

75
00:07:57,101 --> 00:07:58,978
Right, scraggles?

76
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:02,607
My name isn't scraggles.

77
00:08:07,528 --> 00:08:09,489
I'm Togame.

78
00:08:09,572 --> 00:08:10,948
Jo Togame.

79
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:15,369
Fine.

80
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:22,210
Let's do this for real.

81
00:08:23,753 --> 00:08:25,213
Sakura.

82
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:01,832
What the hell is going on?

83
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:03,251
Those two...

84
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:05,169
They're smiling.

85
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:51,966
Sakura-kun...

86
00:09:52,049 --> 00:09:54,427
You're really an amazing guy, huh?

87
00:09:56,929 --> 00:09:59,265
I don't know why...

88
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:02,685
but I'm so touched right now.

89
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:06,856
I didn't expect Sakura to be able
to take it this far.

90
00:10:06,939 --> 00:10:08,065
Yeah.

91
00:10:24,123 --> 00:10:25,583
<i>Damn it.</i>

92
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:27,627
<i>What's this?</i>

93
00:10:29,545 --> 00:10:33,132
<i>I'm fighting just another lame guy,
aren't I?</i>

94
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,887
<i>But why does this feel so good?</i>

95
00:10:39,221 --> 00:10:40,556
<i>Also...</i>

96
00:10:41,682 --> 00:10:44,185
<i>this is probably the first time...</i>

97
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:46,103
Let's do this for real.

98
00:10:46,187 --> 00:10:47,063
Sakura.

99
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:51,108
<i>...I've been called by my name like that.</i>

100
00:10:56,405 --> 00:10:57,740
<i>Good grief.</i>

101
00:10:58,616 --> 00:11:01,619
<i>You look like you're really enjoying this.
It's pissing me off.</i>

102
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:07,708
<i>Your movements are getting even better.</i>

103
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:11,629
Come at me!

104
00:11:51,335 --> 00:11:52,670
I didn't know...

105
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:56,298
fighting could feel this good.

106
00:11:57,675 --> 00:11:59,260
I agree.

107
00:11:59,343 --> 00:12:00,803
This is a first for me, too.

108
00:12:03,722 --> 00:12:06,809
You've kept up with me
for long enough, so...

109
00:12:08,394 --> 00:12:10,062
let's end this.

110
00:12:10,938 --> 00:12:12,440
I agree.

111
00:12:20,072 --> 00:12:21,949
-It's been fun...
-It's been fun...

112
00:12:22,992 --> 00:12:24,243
<i>...Togame.</i>

113
00:12:25,453 --> 00:12:26,620
<i>...Sakura.</i>

114
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:40,009
<i>I see...</i>

115
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:44,305
No matter how strong my opponent is...

116
00:12:44,388 --> 00:12:46,223
even if it's someone I owe my life to...

117
00:12:46,682 --> 00:12:48,100
I won't look away...

118
00:12:49,685 --> 00:12:52,062
or bend my will!

119
00:12:53,314 --> 00:12:54,607
<i>That day...</i>

120
00:12:59,361 --> 00:13:01,864
<i>this is what I should've done.</i>

121
00:13:04,241 --> 00:13:06,452
<i>But I looked away.</i>

122
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:09,914
<i>I never faced him properly.</i>

123
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:13,709
<i>I didn't push my own will onto him.</i>

124
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:18,672
<i>I'm sure you'll become stronger
from here on out...</i>

125
00:13:20,007 --> 00:13:24,136
<i>because you aren't scared of pushing
yourself, no matter your opponent.</i>

126
00:13:26,764 --> 00:13:28,599
<i>Don't you ever change.</i>

127
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:34,480
<i>Thank you...</i>

128
00:13:38,025 --> 00:13:39,235
<i>Sakura.</i>

129
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:45,324
<i>I finally understand.</i>

130
00:13:52,915 --> 00:13:54,833
I can't stand up anymore.

131
00:13:57,628 --> 00:13:59,088
I give up.

132
00:14:12,977 --> 00:14:14,520
Huh? What did he say?

133
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:15,646
He's giving up?

134
00:14:15,729 --> 00:14:17,189
You're kidding me!

135
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:20,526
Togame is a guy who'd smile
and break his way through anything!

136
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:22,319
There has to be a mistake!

137
00:14:22,403 --> 00:14:23,320
Yeah...

138
00:14:24,989 --> 00:14:27,283
Sakura-san...

139
00:14:34,832 --> 00:14:36,083
Screw you!

140
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,628
What the hell did you just say?

141
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:42,047
You're giving up?

142
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:44,466
Why did you lose on purpose...

143
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:47,887
Okay! Great job, both of you!

144
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:50,055
You're really strong!

145
00:14:50,139 --> 00:14:52,099
Fight me next, okay?

146
00:14:52,182 --> 00:14:53,517
Come on, Ume-chan!

147
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:56,562
-It's finally our turn!
-Wait, I'm still...

148
00:14:56,645 --> 00:14:57,479
Choji.

149
00:14:57,563 --> 00:14:59,440
-Hurry! Hurry!
-Let's stop this.

150
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:03,903
-Hey, Ume-chan! Ume-chan, hurry!
-We have no justice to this fight.

151
00:15:03,986 --> 00:15:05,195
Hey, come on!

152
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:07,364
-We...
-I can't wait!

153
00:15:07,448 --> 00:15:09,408
-No, I was wrong.
-Come on, hurry!

154
00:15:09,491 --> 00:15:10,451
Come on, come on!

155
00:15:10,534 --> 00:15:11,368
Choji...

156
00:15:11,452 --> 00:15:13,120
Let's do this already!

157
00:15:22,671 --> 00:15:25,174
Gosh, just shut up.

158
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:27,718
You already lost, so stay quiet.

159
00:15:37,311 --> 00:15:38,771
Sakura.

160
00:15:38,854 --> 00:15:40,189
I'm switching in.

161
00:15:45,778 --> 00:15:47,112
Good.

162
00:15:47,196 --> 00:15:49,406
It seems you've talked your heart out.

163
00:15:50,407 --> 00:15:54,828
What you're doing right now
is indisputable proof of that.

164
00:15:58,415 --> 00:16:01,835
Will you let me handle the rest, Togame?

165
00:16:02,753 --> 00:16:03,837
Please?

166
00:16:10,094 --> 00:16:12,972
You sure like poking your nose
in other people's business.

167
00:16:20,646 --> 00:16:22,523
Don't die on us, okay?

168
00:16:28,612 --> 00:16:29,947
If you lose...

169
00:16:31,115 --> 00:16:32,408
I'll kick your ass.

170
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:35,035
Got it.

171
00:16:36,328 --> 00:16:38,580
<i>Why did that piss me off so hard?</i>

172
00:16:40,457 --> 00:16:43,794
<i>I've seen enough people
getting beaten in front of my eyes.</i>

173
00:16:45,504 --> 00:16:47,047
<i>And yet, why...</i>

174
00:16:47,756 --> 00:16:49,091
<i>Good.</i>

175
00:16:49,174 --> 00:16:51,552
<i>It seems you've talked your heart out.</i>

176
00:16:51,635 --> 00:16:53,679
<i>This makes no sense.</i>

177
00:16:54,221 --> 00:16:56,849
<i>I didn't hear any words from his fists...</i>

178
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,226
Sakura-san!

179
00:17:03,939 --> 00:17:05,858
Welcome back.

180
00:17:05,941 --> 00:17:08,027
You're crying again, Nirei-kun.

181
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:11,113
That was an amazing fight! I was so moved!

182
00:17:11,196 --> 00:17:12,239
Sakura.

183
00:17:13,157 --> 00:17:15,701
I'm sure you're not happy
with how that turned out...

184
00:17:15,784 --> 00:17:18,412
but that was Togame's way
of settling his debts.

185
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:21,373
And even taking that out of the equation...

186
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:24,710
you did great out there.

187
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:32,426
Come on, Ume-chan!

188
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:35,137
We can finally have our fight!

189
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:39,767
I've got something to ask you first.

190
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:43,812
Did you not feel anything
from the earlier fight?

191
00:17:43,896 --> 00:17:45,439
Huh? Feel what?

192
00:17:49,026 --> 00:17:50,194
I see.

193
00:17:52,863 --> 00:17:54,239
That's a shame.

194
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:11,256
A shame?

195
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:14,259
Why's that?

196
00:18:19,556 --> 00:18:20,766
Oh, well!

197
00:18:20,849 --> 00:18:24,561
Anyway, Ume-chan! You're so unfair!

198
00:18:25,187 --> 00:18:28,565
You have so many strong guys in Bofurin!

199
00:18:29,233 --> 00:18:31,318
We're nothing like you guys.

200
00:18:32,027 --> 00:18:35,948
I can't be free because
everyone here is so weak.

201
00:18:37,074 --> 00:18:38,700
It's no fun.

202
00:18:41,161 --> 00:18:42,830
What the hell, man?

203
00:18:43,288 --> 00:18:46,333
Is that how Tomiyama-san sees us?

204
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:48,335
But if I win...

205
00:18:48,836 --> 00:18:51,213
The Ume-chan... and Furin...

206
00:18:52,172 --> 00:18:55,384
all of this will become mine!

207
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,846
You're the top of Furin.

208
00:18:59,513 --> 00:19:02,432
<i>You're stronger and freer
than anyone else.</i>

209
00:19:02,516 --> 00:19:05,227
<i>That's why you're always
having so much fun, right?</i>

210
00:19:05,978 --> 00:19:09,481
If I can prove that I'm stronger than you,

211
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:12,067
and get my hands on Furin...

212
00:19:12,151 --> 00:19:16,405
I'll finally be free and
be happier than anyone else

213
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:19,533
Finally...

214
00:19:20,492 --> 00:19:22,035
Finally...

215
00:19:25,164 --> 00:19:28,458
This boring life will finally end.

216
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:34,715
Now, Ume-chan...

217
00:19:35,549 --> 00:19:36,884
give it...

218
00:19:38,218 --> 00:19:40,804
to me!

219
00:20:13,921 --> 00:20:17,549
I've never seen someone
move that absurdly before.

220
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:19,593
He's a natural-born monster.

221
00:20:19,676 --> 00:20:24,723
He is the youngest kid
to ever be the leader of Shishitoren.

222
00:20:25,641 --> 00:20:28,060
<i>Dammit... Dammit...</i>

223
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:32,356
<i>If only he didn't stop me...</i>

224
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:39,529
<i>Then he and I...</i>

225
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:40,989
<i>Dammit!</i>

226
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:44,117
<i>I'll become stronger!</i>

227
00:20:46,328 --> 00:20:47,579
<i>Stronger...</i>

228
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:49,623
<i>Even stronger!</i>

229
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:08,141
Hey, Tomiyama.

230
00:21:08,225 --> 00:21:09,726
What is it, Ume-chan?

231
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:14,439
Talking about all these "what ifs"
will not make it any less hard for you.

232
00:21:17,526 --> 00:21:20,279
You've got it hard, huh, Tomiyama?

233
00:21:22,447 --> 00:21:24,992
Like I said...

234
00:21:25,659 --> 00:21:27,953
I just don't...

235
00:21:28,787 --> 00:21:31,164
understand what you're trying to say!

236
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:40,799
I see.

237
00:21:41,925 --> 00:21:43,760
So you don't understand, huh?

238
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:50,559
If you can't even understand
something so simple...

239
00:21:51,685 --> 00:21:53,562
then there is absolutely no way...

240
00:21:55,939 --> 00:21:57,149
I'll lose.

241
00:23:31,409 --> 00:23:34,621
Tomiyama-san's acrobatic moves
are amazing!

242
00:23:35,413 --> 00:23:37,457
Even I can do that much.

243
00:23:37,541 --> 00:23:40,377
Really? Wow! Let me see you do it!

244
00:23:40,460 --> 00:23:42,420
Huh? Like, right now?

245
00:23:42,504 --> 00:23:43,547
Yes, now!

246
00:23:45,841 --> 00:23:47,509
Oh, so you can't do it?

247
00:23:48,426 --> 00:23:51,179
You say what?
Just you watch! I'll do it now!

248
00:23:51,263 --> 00:23:52,848
-Yay!
-Let's go!

249
00:23:52,931 --> 00:23:55,559
Three, two, one...

250
00:23:55,642 --> 00:23:57,185
Hold up!

251
00:23:57,269 --> 00:24:00,480
I'll do it on my own mark. One, two...

